cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.DB, cs.IR, cs.CL. 

The paper proposes an algorithm for learning embedding vectors from real world EMR data based medical knowledge, which involves machine learning and natural language processing techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves enhancements to existing algorithms and loss calculation, which falls under the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of medical knowledge graph and training data set augmentation relates to cs.DB (Databases). The link prediction task and verification of the algorithm on real world EMR data falls under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) respectively.
